      <p style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--ink-3);line-height:1.7;margin:0">Four fixed layers behind everything: <b style="color:var(--ink-2)">starfield</b>, <b style="color:var(--ink-2)">scanlines</b>, film <b style="color:var(--ink-2)">grain</b>, and a <b style="color:var(--ink-2)">vignette</b>.</p>
      <span class="cap">Subtle &mdash; it sets mood, never competes with content.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cell"><div class="cell-t">Chrome &mdash; Y2K bezel</div>
      <div class="cell-row"><span class="chip-glyph bezel">&#9678;</span><span class="chip-glyph bezel">&#9670;</span><span class="chip-glyph bezel">&#9632;</span><span class="chip-glyph bezel">&#9670;&#9670;</span></div>
      <span class="cap">Silver gradient-border chips &mdash; the Sony hardware tell.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- ════════════════════ TYPOGRAPHY ════════════════════ -->
<section class="sec" id="type">
  <div class="sec-h"><span class="ix">01</span><h2>Typography</h2></div>
  <p class="sec-sub">Section headings are set in Microgramma (loaded as <b>Michroma</b>) for a wide squared character; Saira carries display and sub-heading text. Both take a white&rarr;lilac gradient sheen. Numerics use the mono face with tabular figures; headline values glow as LCD readouts. Body stays in Inter and is used sparingly.</p>

  <div class="grid cols-2">
    <div class="cell pad-lg"><div class="cell-t">Display &amp; headings</div>
      <div class="col" style="gap:14px">
        <div style="font-family:var(--head);font-weight:400;font-size:33px;letter-spacing:.015em;line-height:1.05;text-transform:uppercase;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#fff 50%,#C7C8F6 150%);-webkit-background-clip:text;background-clip:text;color:transparent">Command Deck</div>
        <div class="display-l">Saira display L</div>
        <div class="eyebrow">Stagecoach league &#183; <b>week 14</b></div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.65;margin:0;max-width:42ch">Body copy in Inter. Used for descriptions and prose, kept short so the interface chrome and data stay dominant.</p>
      </div>
      <span class="cap"><b>Headings</b> Microgramma / <code>Michroma</code> · <code>--head</code> &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp; <b>display</b> Saira · <code>.display-xl/.display-l</code> &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp; gradient text-clip</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cell pad-lg"><div class="cell-t">Numerics &amp; readouts</div>
      <div class="row between" style="margin-bottom:16px"><div class="lcd"><small>&#9672;</small> 12,480</div><div class="lcd lilac">63%</div></div>
      <div class="row" style="gap:22px;margin-bottom:16px"><span class="metric">118.4</span><span class="metric up">&#9650; +9.2</span><span class="metric dn">&#9660; &minus;3.1</span></div>
      <div class="row gap6"><span class="kbd">&#8984;K</span><span class="kbd">&#8679;</span><span class="kbd">ESC</span><span class="kbd">&#9166;</span></div>
      <span class="cap"><code>.lcd</code> (amber glow) · <code>.metric</code> tabular · <code>.kbd</code> keycaps</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid cols-3 mt16">
    <div class="cell span2"><div class="cell-t">Notebook / code block &mdash; syntax tint</div>
      <div class="nb"><span class="c"># read · week-14 · model v4.2</span>
<span class="k">for</span> game <span class="k">in</span> slate.sunday(<span class="s">"early"</span>):
    edge = model.price(game) - market.line
    <span class="k">if</span> edge &gt; THRESHOLD:        <span class="c"># 4.0%</span>
        flag(game, conf=<span class="f">calibrate</span>(edge))
<span class="c"># top signal &rarr;</span> <span class="n">BELL</span> anytime-td <span class="c">+4.4%</span></div>
      <span class="cap">Comments <code>--ink-4</code> · keywords lilac · strings steel · numbers amber · fns jade</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cell"><div class="cell-t">Inline tags</div>
      <div class="col" style="gap:9px">
        <div class="row gap6"><span class="tag p0">P0</span><span class="tag p1">P1</span><span class="tag p2">P2</span></div>
        <div class="row gap6"><span class="badge b-li">START</span><span class="badge b-fl">FLEX</span><span class="badge b-fa">FADE</span></div>
        <div class="row gap6"><span class="edge pos">+4.4%</span><span class="edge neg">&minus;0.9%</span><span class="edge flat">EVEN</span></div>
      </div>
      <span class="cap">Priority tags, verdict badges, edge pills.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════════════════════ SURFACES ════════════════════ -->
<section class="sec" id="surfaces">
  <div class="sec-h"><span class="ix">02</span><h2>Surfaces</h2></div>
  <p class="sec-sub">Containers are glass panels floating over the atmosphere. Headers carry a mono label and an optional bezel glyph; a centered readout marks a focused or hero panel.</p>

  <div class="grid cols-3">
    <div class="cell"><div class="cell-t">Glass panel</div>
      <div class="panel"><div class="panel-h"><span class="chip-glyph bezel" style="width:24px;height:24px;font-size:11px">&#9636;</span><span class="pt">Telemetry</span><span class="px">LIVE</span></div>
        <div class="panel-b"><p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink-3);margin:0;line-height:1.6">Translucent surface, hairline border, bevel + soft drop shadow.</p></div></div>
      <span class="cap"><code>.panel</code> + <code>.panel-h</code> / <code>.panel-b</code></span>
    </div>
    <div class="cell"><div class="cell-t">Hero panel &mdash; centered readout</div>
      <div class="panel" style="padding:18px;text-align:center">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px">win probability</div>
        <div class="gauge-v">63%<small>favored</small></div>
      </div>
      <span class="cap">Glass <code>.panel</code> + centered <code>.gauge-v</code> for a focal readout.</span>
    </div>
